body:
@cbickel does https://github.com/apache/incubator-openwhisk/pull/3671#issuecomment-392007532 address your concerns?

if we adopt the nginx generated id as the activation id, then this pr becomes a lot simpler.
we can also remove the double headers currently generated by the controller (and only emit it if an id isn't received).

@chetanmeh that should indeed be possible, will require quite some work on top of this (i.e. the list would need to be rewritten while not buffering too much).

Rewriting a stream from CouchDB could be done with https://developer.lightbend.com/docs/alpakka/current/data-transformations/json.html#streaming-of-nested-structures for example.

In general, I see this as a subsequent PR though. I agree with the general idea, I believe we can do this separately though.
